WEBVTT

00:36.871 --> 00:38.862
MOHINDER:
Where does it come from?

00:38.956 --> 00:42.949
This quest, this need
to solve life’s mysteries,

00:43.044 --> 00:46.787
when the simplest of questions
can never be answered?

00:48.424 --> 00:52.793
Why are we here?
What is the soul?
Why do we dream?

00:55.139 --> 00:58.097
Perhaps we’d be better off
not looking at all.

00:58.184 --> 01:00.300
Not delving, not yearning.

01:02.521 --> 01:06.309
That’s not human nature.
Not the human heart.

01:08.611 --> 01:10.943
That is not why we are here.

01:26.921 --> 01:28.752
How's he doing?

01:30.675 --> 01:32.211
I'm sorry.
Did I scare you?

01:32.301 --> 01:33.290
No.

01:34.387 --> 01:38.050
No, Ijust... I keep having
these amazing dreams
every time | close my eyes,

01:38.140 --> 01:41.348
and... Never mind.

01:42.853 --> 01:45.595
He likes me to read him
the stock page.

01:45.690 --> 01:48.102
Has he been conscious at all?
No.

01:49.443 --> 01:51.934
Been a week now.
I think he's close.

01:52.029 --> 01:53.405
A couple more
days, maybe.

01:56.993 --> 01:59.951
Excuse me.
You know, I don't know
what he'd do without you.

02:00.037 --> 02:02.289
You got a real gift.
Just doing myjob.

02:02.373 --> 02:04.364
No, you're like
a son to him.

02:05.626 --> 02:07.662
Now, that'd make us
like brother and sister.

02:07.753 --> 02:10.711
Might be... Might be
a little awkward if I ever
wanted to ask you out.

02:14.677 --> 02:17.339
I'm sorry, that was...
That was inappropriate.

02:17.430 --> 02:19.216
No, it's sweet, it's...

02:19.682 --> 02:21.297
I'm dating somebody.

02:21.392 --> 02:23.508
Yeah. No, really,
it's okay.

02:27.982 --> 02:30.098
I need to change his lV.

02:30.484 --> 02:32.395
I'm sorry, of course.

02:36.073 --> 02:39.065
Man is a narcissistic
species by nature.

02:39.785 --> 02:43.243
We have colonized the four
corners of our tiny planet.

02:43.331 --> 02:46.539
But we are not the pinnacle
of so-called evolution.

02:46.792 --> 02:49.579
That honor belongs
to the lowly cockroach.

02:49.962 --> 02:52.669
Capable of living for months
without food.

02:52.757 --> 02:56.966
Remaining alive headless
for weeks at a time.
Resistant to radiation.

02:57.303 --> 03:00.466
If God has indeed created
himself in his own image,

03:00.556 --> 03:03.468
then I submit to you
that God is a cockroach.

03:08.564 --> 03:12.102
They say that man uses
only a tenth
of his brainpower.

03:12.818 --> 03:16.731
Another percent and we might
actually be worthy
of God's image.

03:18.115 --> 03:21.107
Unless, of course, that day
has already arrived.

03:21.285 --> 03:24.869
The Human Genome Project
has discovered
that tiny variations

03:24.955 --> 03:29.039
in man's genetic code
are taking place
at increasingly rapid rates.

03:30.044 --> 03:33.127
Teleportation, levitation,
tissue regeneration.

03:33.422 --> 03:35.754
Is this outside the realm
of possibility?

03:35.841 --> 03:38.878
Or is man entering
a new gateway to evolution?

03:39.220 --> 03:43.680
Is he finally standing
at the threshold
to true human potential?

03:46.727 --> 03:48.809
I'm sorry, I'm out of time.

03:54.819 --> 03:58.311
I know, I know. I'm beginning
to sound like my father.
I can't help it.

03:58.406 --> 04:00.738
You know, they can fire
me, too, if they like,

04:00.825 --> 04:04.158
but there is
something to it, Nirad,
as crazy as it sounds.

04:06.664 --> 04:07.824
What is it?

04:09.125 --> 04:12.288
It's your father.
He's dead.

04:16.465 --> 04:17.500
How?

04:17.591 --> 04:20.583
NIRAD: Driving a taxi
in New York City
is a very dangerous job.

04:20.678 --> 04:22.134
The wrong fare,
the wrong time.

04:22.221 --> 04:23.927
We may never know
what really happened.

04:24.014 --> 04:25.515
No, I spoke to him
two days ago.

04:25.599 --> 04:27.055
He was convinced
someone was following him,

04:27.143 --> 04:28.428
trying to steal
his research.

04:28.519 --> 04:29.679
He died because
of his theories!

04:29.812 --> 04:31.348
That's crazy!
Is it?

04:32.273 --> 04:34.059
The man left his family,

04:34.150 --> 04:37.187
discredited his career,
to chase wild theories
halfway around the world!

04:37.319 --> 04:40.857
Where are you going?
To his apartment, to get
his papers, his research!

04:41.031 --> 04:43.192
He was this close
to finding the
first of them.

04:43.284 --> 04:45.866
His Patient Zero,
he tracked him
to Queens, New York.

04:45.995 --> 04:47.656
Mohinder, listen to me.

04:47.746 --> 04:50.123
Your father was my colleague
and my friend.

04:50.207 --> 04:52.493
A respected professor,
a brilliant geneticist.

04:52.585 --> 04:54.746
But he had clearly
lost touch with reality!

04:54.837 --> 04:56.418
I've followed
in his footsteps.

04:56.505 --> 04:58.006
My thesis is based
on his research!

04:58.090 --> 04:59.876
Yes, you always wanted
his approval!

04:59.967 --> 05:01.958
And now you're
telling me that it
was all for nothing.

05:02.052 --> 05:04.043
I'm telling you to let go.

05:04.138 --> 05:08.677
I need to know why he died.
I need to know that it
wasn't all for nothing.

05:09.143 --> 05:12.010
And then I need to finish
what he started.

06:08.702 --> 06:10.363
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

06:12.414 --> 06:13.403
Hello?

06:14.625 --> 06:16.661
Yeah, yeah,
I'm at his place now.

06:17.878 --> 06:20.460
No,no,no,heleﬁ
everything behind
but his computer.

06:20.548 --> 06:22.288
Research, the map.

06:22.633 --> 06:25.966
Yeah, let's get a team
in here to bag and tag
everything.

06:26.929 --> 06:29.136
I gotta call you
right back.

07:01.589 --> 07:03.170
(MUSTANG SALLY PLAYING)

07:29.199 --> 07:30.530
(BEEPING)

07:58.270 --> 07:59.259
Pervert.

08:23.420 --> 08:25.502
Time to get up, Micah!

08:28.801 --> 08:30.086
Micah!

08:35.391 --> 08:36.631
Micah!

08:37.726 --> 08:40.263
Micah! Micah!

08:40.354 --> 08:41.594
What?

08:41.939 --> 08:43.395
Damn it, Micah,
don't do that to me.

08:43.482 --> 08:44.471
Do what?

08:44.817 --> 08:47.775
Just you need
to be careful.
All right?

08:48.195 --> 08:50.527
I'm just working
on my computer.

08:50.614 --> 08:53.777
The logic board was bad,
so I had to build a new one.

08:54.827 --> 08:56.112
A new one.

08:57.621 --> 09:00.704
Did anyone ever tell you
you're the smartest little
man on the planet?

09:00.791 --> 09:02.622
You do.
All the time.

09:06.714 --> 09:08.420
What's this?

09:08.507 --> 09:11.374
It's a pinhole camera.
It's for the eclipse.

09:13.220 --> 09:15.506
The moon's gonna cover up
the sun today.

09:15.597 --> 09:16.928
We're supposed
to look at it
atschoo!

09:17.015 --> 09:21.349
Speaking of which,
you need to go get ready.
Can't be late, not today.

09:21.437 --> 09:24.224
Mom, I'm already dressed
and I've packed my own lunch.

09:24.314 --> 09:27.272
That's what I've been
doing this morning.
What about you?

09:27.359 --> 09:29.395
Don't get smart with me.

09:29.737 --> 09:31.568
All right, I've been
working to pay our bills.

09:31.655 --> 09:33.441
Yeah, that's why they
turned off our gas again?

09:33.532 --> 09:34.942
(DOORBELL RINGING)

09:35.492 --> 09:37.699
Go grab your stuff
and wait by the back door,
okay?

09:37.786 --> 09:39.651
Why?
Just do it.

09:48.505 --> 09:49.756
Mom, what's going on?

09:49.840 --> 09:52.252
Never mind, just keep
your voice down
and stay close to me.

09:52.342 --> 09:53.673
(POUNDING ON DOOR)

10:19.536 --> 10:20.946
Camera ready?

10:21.038 --> 10:22.824
MAN: Yeah, almost! Hold on!

10:23.373 --> 10:26.536
This looks like 70, 80 feet.
This is so unreal.

10:26.627 --> 10:27.833
Okay, I'm good!

10:29.421 --> 10:31.377
Okay. Oh my...

10:31.465 --> 10:32.454
(SCREAMING)

10:32.549 --> 10:35.006
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God! Claire?

10:36.220 --> 10:37.505
Oh, my God.

10:41.558 --> 10:42.547
Claire!

10:56.740 --> 11:00.073
This is Claire Bennet
and that was attempt
number six.

11:40.242 --> 11:42.278
DRIVER: You get out here, yes?

11:47.833 --> 11:50.199
Mr. Linderman, I'm gonna
have to call you back
in five minutes, okay?

11:50.294 --> 11:51.329
Thank you.

11:51.420 --> 11:53.786
I'm late. I've got
a fundraiser and a
drinks meeting. What is it?

11:53.881 --> 11:55.371
Ithappened
two more times.

11:55.465 --> 11:57.501
Sometimes I'm falling,
sometimes I'm flying.

11:57.634 --> 11:59.795
Sometimes you're in 'em.
I don't have time
for this now.

11:59.887 --> 12:01.798
They're not just dreams,
Nathan!

12:01.889 --> 12:03.220
Hold this.

12:03.307 --> 12:04.717
I thought they'd go away,
but they're not!

12:04.808 --> 12:06.264
Jim, I need this
back by 6:00, please.
Thanks.

12:06.351 --> 12:09.343
This morning when I got out
of bed, my foot hovered
before it hit the ground.

12:09.438 --> 12:12.271
Hovered!
For a split second,
like I was floating.

12:12.774 --> 12:14.981
I'm telling you,
I think I can fly!

12:17.821 --> 12:19.857
These all undecideds?
Mmm-hmm.

12:20.032 --> 12:22.899
Tell you what, you think
you can fly? Why don't you
jump off the Brooklyn Bridge?

12:22.993 --> 12:23.948
See what happens.

12:24.036 --> 12:26.823
Maybe I ought to
start with something
a little lower first.

12:26.914 --> 12:28.370
Just like learning to walk.
You're serious.

12:28.457 --> 12:31.324
Oh, I'm serious.
You need to snap
out of it, Peter.

12:31.418 --> 12:33.329
Go see a doctor,
get some drugs.

12:33.670 --> 12:35.706
But do not pull
a Roger Clinton
on me, man,

12:35.797 --> 12:37.128
I'm eight points down
in the polls!

12:37.215 --> 12:38.796
Look, this isn't
about you, all right?

12:38.884 --> 12:41.216
Look, something
is happening to me,
and l have this feeling

12:41.303 --> 12:43.134
that you're the only person
that's gonna understand this!

12:43.221 --> 12:46.349
Why the hell would
I understand that
you think you can fly?

12:46.516 --> 12:49.428
(CELL PHONE RINGING)
Because you're
my brother!

12:50.520 --> 12:53.011
Mom, I can't talk...
What?

12:53.690 --> 12:55.476
I'll be there in 10 minutes.

12:55.567 --> 12:57.273
What'd she do now?

12:58.528 --> 13:00.484
She got arrested.
Arrested for what?

13:00.572 --> 13:01.607
Shoplifting.

13:02.783 --> 13:04.523
I'm so depressed.

13:05.118 --> 13:07.404
What? What are you talking
about? Why?

13:09.039 --> 13:12.497
I mean, I mean, besides
the fact that it was so gross
that I almost fudged myself,

13:12.584 --> 13:16.076
this is the single coolest
thing to happen to this town
in, like, 100 years.

13:16.171 --> 13:18.583
Not if nobody finds out,
it's not.

13:19.967 --> 13:21.423
Why'd you want me
to tape it?

13:21.510 --> 13:23.046
I have my reasons.

13:24.805 --> 13:27.968
It's not like you're not
gonna be popular anymore.

13:28.058 --> 13:29.047
Popular?

13:29.768 --> 13:31.850
Who said anything
about being popular?

13:31.937 --> 13:34.144
My life as I know it
is over, okay?

13:34.231 --> 13:37.268
I've got the Bishop game
next week, SAT's in October,

13:37.359 --> 13:39.270
Homecoming's
three weeks from today,
and I'm a freak show!

13:39.361 --> 13:40.976
You're being a little
dramatic, don't you think?

13:41.071 --> 13:43.062
No, I don't think!

13:43.198 --> 13:45.735
I have busted, like,
every bone in my body,

13:45.826 --> 13:49.193
stabbed myself in the chest,
I've shoved a two-foot
steel rod through my neck,

13:49.287 --> 13:51.414
and I don't have
a scratch on me!

13:51.498 --> 13:53.739
What do you call
that thing sticking out?

13:55.210 --> 13:56.916
Oh, great.

14:03.593 --> 14:06.676
Just give me
the tape, okay?
Sure.

14:13.395 --> 14:16.353
Hey, I can give you a ride
on my handlebars if you want.

14:16.606 --> 14:18.187
(SIGHING)

14:18.775 --> 14:21.232
Look, thanks, okay?

14:21.778 --> 14:25.270
I'll talk to you
in front of people
at school tomorrow.

14:25.657 --> 14:26.897
Promise.

15:16.416 --> 15:18.156
(SPEAKING IN JAPANESE)

16:16.184 --> 16:18.140
(MUSTANG SALLY PLAYING)

16:25.861 --> 16:29.103
Your son is
a very intelligent boy.

16:29.197 --> 16:32.485
Gifted, actually.
That's not the issue.

16:32.742 --> 16:35.950
His father's not around,
and sometimes I think
he could use

16:36.037 --> 16:37.868
a bit of a stronger hand,
you know?

16:40.417 --> 16:44.410
I work nights a lot,
but we can both work harder.

16:45.297 --> 16:47.253
It's not about the work.

16:47.340 --> 16:51.754
The truth is, Ijust don't
know if this school
is the right fit for him.

16:52.095 --> 16:54.211
But he's made friends.
I'm sorry.

16:55.974 --> 16:58.010
He's on the soccer team.
I'm sorry.

16:58.101 --> 17:02.265
I wrote a check
for $25,000 to get him
into this snob fest.

17:02.689 --> 17:04.520
I was told that
that's what it took.

17:04.608 --> 17:06.144
That's on top
of the tuition.

17:06.234 --> 17:09.897
About the tuition.
Your last three checks
have bounced.

17:10.280 --> 17:12.396
Fine, take it out
of the 25 grand
that I gave you.

17:12.490 --> 17:15.653
That was a donation.
And it was very appreciated.

17:15.785 --> 17:20.119
Well, I want my money back.
I want my money back, now.

17:20.207 --> 17:22.323
That money went
to the capital campaign
for the new wing.

17:22.417 --> 17:24.203
It's already been spent.
Then unspend it!

17:24.294 --> 17:25.283
I'm sorry.

17:25.629 --> 17:28.996
We could maybe discuss
an extension of the money
that you owe, but...

17:31.176 --> 17:32.962
I want my money back.

17:33.178 --> 17:35.760
That's not possible.

17:38.475 --> 17:40.011
Come on, baby,
let's get out of here.

17:40.143 --> 17:41.679
You're too good
for this lousy school.

17:47.067 --> 17:48.056
Mom?

17:50.654 --> 17:52.519
Leave me alone!

17:58.161 --> 17:59.776
For God's sake, Ma.

18:00.580 --> 18:01.911
Are you okay?

18:01.998 --> 18:03.204
They dropped the charges.

18:03.291 --> 18:04.792
I have to fill out a form.
No big deal.

18:04.876 --> 18:06.161
No big deal?
I'm running for Congress.

18:06.253 --> 18:09.416
Do you have any idea what this
is gonna do to me if it gets
out, with our family's past?

18:09.506 --> 18:13.044
What could you possibly
need so bad that
you had to steal it?

18:13.134 --> 18:14.385
Never mind,
I don't wanna know.

18:14.469 --> 18:16.175
Socks.
Socks?

18:18.390 --> 18:20.255
Dad left you a fortune.
What are you thinking?

18:20.350 --> 18:22.181
You know, it's been one
ridiculous stunt
after another with you

18:22.269 --> 18:25.261
for the last six months!
Dad's gone, just get over it!

18:25.355 --> 18:26.686
You know what?
Leave her alone!

18:26.773 --> 18:28.138
She's okay,
that's all that matters.

18:28.233 --> 18:29.894
I gotta keep this
out of the press.

18:31.778 --> 18:33.018
You know what?
Just get out of here.

18:33.113 --> 18:34.694
Go worry
about your image,
I'll handle this.

18:34.864 --> 18:37.480
Yeah. Good.
I gotta make sure
this stays buried.

18:38.201 --> 18:40.317
Thanks a lot, Mom.
Mmm-hmm.

18:45.959 --> 18:47.324
What were you thinking?

18:48.253 --> 18:50.710
I just wanted to feel
alive again.

18:55.885 --> 18:57.671
Nathan only cares
about himself.

18:57.762 --> 19:01.380
Your father was the same way.
Alpha dogs, both of them.

19:01.850 --> 19:05.217
You, in the meantime,
for all your selflessness,

19:05.312 --> 19:08.054
and sitting
with dying people...

19:08.898 --> 19:11.480
What? You're gonna retire
on what you make?

19:11.568 --> 19:14.480
Maybe I'll shoplift my socks.
Don't get smart.

19:14.571 --> 19:17.483
When you put everyone
else first, you end up last.

19:17.574 --> 19:20.031
You always put Nathan first,
he took advantage.

19:20.118 --> 19:23.451
Yeah, it wasn't you
that was just pushing him
right out in front of me?

19:23.538 --> 19:26.951
He takes up
more space than you.
Demanded more attention.

19:27.417 --> 19:29.373
And besides, it's not
my fault, you allowed it.

19:29.461 --> 19:31.417
He's my brother.
I love him.

19:31.504 --> 19:33.415
Ah, love is overrated.

19:33.715 --> 19:36.081
He loves me, too.
I know him.

19:36.634 --> 19:39.171
We've always been close.
Rose-colored glasses.

19:39.262 --> 19:40.763
That's cruel, Mom!

19:42.432 --> 19:45.139
Look, since Dad died, I know
you've been feeling free
to speak your mind,

19:45.226 --> 19:48.639
but it wouldn't hurt
to edit yourself
every once in a while.

19:48.730 --> 19:50.812
I'm sorry
if the truth hurts.

19:51.733 --> 19:54.770
I'm just saying
you hero-worshipped him.

19:55.111 --> 19:56.976
And those feelings
were never returned.

19:57.072 --> 20:00.314
You're wrong!
It's biological,
and I can't help it,

20:01.368 --> 20:02.778
we're connected.

20:06.915 --> 20:10.703
I never told you this,
but when Nathan
had his accident,

20:11.378 --> 20:12.618
I knew it.

20:12.670 --> 20:15.457
We all got the same call.
No, I'm saying
before the call,

20:15.548 --> 20:18.290
like he was telling me,
300 miles away.

20:18.385 --> 20:21.593
lwoke up, and I knew
that he'd been hurt.

20:28.853 --> 20:32.516
I hate it here.
She doesn't even have
any books to read.

20:32.607 --> 20:35.223
Baby, I'll be right back,
I'm just gonna go and
pack up a few things.

20:35.318 --> 20:37.434
We should really
go see Dad.

20:37.821 --> 20:39.357
What good would that do?

20:39.447 --> 20:42.314
He could help.
He should know that
someone's trying to hurt us.

20:42.409 --> 20:45.651
Your dad's not in any position
to help us right now.

20:45.912 --> 20:48.779
Look, I made some mistakes,
I admit it.

20:48.873 --> 20:50.488
Mom, what'd you do?

20:53.586 --> 20:58.296
Hey. I need you to know
that I would never let
anything happen to you.

20:58.675 --> 20:59.915
Promise.

21:00.009 --> 21:03.467
Mom, why'd you look
at yourself like that
in the fish tank?

21:06.516 --> 21:07.847
(SIGHS)

21:11.521 --> 21:14.137
How long?
Just a couple hours, tops.

21:14.232 --> 21:16.689
There's some ice cream
in the fridge.

21:17.152 --> 21:18.437
Go ahead.

21:21.739 --> 21:24.481
What happened?
I went to see Linderman.

21:24.576 --> 21:26.487
How much?
Thirty.

21:26.786 --> 21:29.778
You gambling again?
No, it's just bills.

21:30.123 --> 21:32.205
And I used the rest to get
Micah into private school.

21:32.292 --> 21:35.910
They didn't know what to do
with him at public,
andljust”

21:36.004 --> 21:38.461
I needed them to think
that we had money.

21:38.548 --> 21:40.209
From the mob?

21:41.426 --> 21:42.666
Hell, Niki.

21:43.178 --> 21:46.170
You weren't born yesterday!
I'm just two weeks overdue!

21:46.264 --> 21:48.471
I mean, I thought
that I could handle it,
okay?

21:48.600 --> 21:51.467
I'm under a lot of stress
right now, okay?
Gee, I wonder why?

21:53.730 --> 21:56.062
I feel like I'm kind of
losing it a little bit.

21:59.235 --> 22:01.066
I'm seeing things.

22:01.863 --> 22:02.852
Like?

22:03.823 --> 22:05.734
Like I keep feeling
like someone's watching me.

22:05.825 --> 22:08.032
Yeah, Linderman wants
his money back,

22:08.119 --> 22:10.656
so he sends some
mouth-breather that's gonna
put you in the hospital.

22:10.747 --> 22:12.703
No, it is someone else.

22:14.125 --> 22:16.366
It's someone
that I can't see.

22:19.088 --> 22:21.079
Does this make
any sense to you?

22:25.470 --> 22:26.459
No.

22:29.098 --> 22:31.350
I'm sorry, you know what?
But I'll tell you what does...

22:31.434 --> 22:32.469
I shouldn't be
telling you this.

22:32.560 --> 22:34.096
No, no, let me tell you
what does make sense.

22:34.187 --> 22:38.021
You need to come up
with that 30 grand
plus interest, now.

22:38.107 --> 22:39.688
Or you gotta run.

22:41.277 --> 22:42.392
Watch him.

22:44.614 --> 22:45.603
All right.

23:08.555 --> 23:10.011
Cool, huh?

23:13.268 --> 23:15.304
How hot do you think
it is in there?

23:18.815 --> 23:20.646
Turn on the camera.

24:08.531 --> 24:11.022
Scotty! Scotty! Come on!

24:18.958 --> 24:21.870
Take it easy,
you're all right!
I'm okay, I'm fine!

24:22.754 --> 24:24.085
Take it easy.

24:28.092 --> 24:29.707
There's no burns!

24:32.347 --> 24:33.587
Get going!

24:44.817 --> 24:47.729
One, two, three, four,
five, go!

24:48.571 --> 24:50.152
One, two, three...

24:51.783 --> 24:53.819
MAN: Yeah, I was real sorry
to hear about your father.

24:53.910 --> 24:56.242
He seemed like a good guy.

24:58.247 --> 25:00.829
Man, I thought
I was a slob.

25:01.876 --> 25:03.491
They were here, too.

25:03.586 --> 25:05.201
What?
Nothing.

25:05.296 --> 25:07.082
I got a guy who can clean
this up for 100 bucks.

25:07.173 --> 25:09.414
No. It's all right.
I'll take it as it is.

25:09.509 --> 25:10.919
We rent by the week.

25:11.719 --> 25:13.425
I'm gonna need to know
you can afford it.

25:13.513 --> 25:14.673
I have a job.

25:14.764 --> 25:15.753
Doing what?

25:18.101 --> 25:19.716
Driving a taxi.

25:20.645 --> 25:22.385
I'll get you an application.

26:12.822 --> 26:14.562
MAN ON RAD/O:
In these uncertain times...

26:15.283 --> 26:16.773
We need a leader who...

26:19.954 --> 26:22.991
Nathan Petrelli.
He served his country
in Bosnia.

26:31.132 --> 26:32.417
SIMONE: Hey!

26:34.719 --> 26:37.256
Oh, God. What?
The silent treatment?

26:39.849 --> 26:41.555
Oh, boy.

26:43.478 --> 26:46.686
Isaac? What are you doing?

26:47.982 --> 26:49.688
What the hell is
wrong with you?

26:50.610 --> 26:51.599
Isaac!

26:53.654 --> 26:54.939
Okay, stop!

26:55.198 --> 26:57.154
What... What,
are you crazy?

26:57.241 --> 27:00.699
Clearly.
I don't even remember
painting these.

27:01.621 --> 27:03.953
I was high, okay?
I lied to you.
Damn it.

27:04.791 --> 27:05.780
I've been chasing
for a month.

27:05.875 --> 27:07.365
Well, then, get yourself
back into a program

27:07.460 --> 27:08.950
and make it
stick this time.

27:09.045 --> 27:12.003
These are fantastic!
No! They're evil.

27:12.089 --> 27:13.795
What are you talking about?

27:13.883 --> 27:15.623
What am I talking about?

27:15.718 --> 27:19.381
You know what
I'm talking about?
You see this?

27:20.515 --> 27:23.803
Suicide bombing in Israel.
I painted it three weeks ago.

27:23.893 --> 27:25.008
Yeah, so?

27:26.437 --> 27:28.553
So? That's this
morning's paper.

27:29.190 --> 27:30.600
Look at the number
on the bus.

27:32.652 --> 27:34.643
This happened yesterday.

27:35.738 --> 27:36.727
Yesterday.

27:39.492 --> 27:42.529
Something's wrong with me.

27:43.204 --> 27:44.569
We'll get you help, Isaac.

27:44.664 --> 27:47.406
I tried that, twice.
There's only one way left.

27:47.792 --> 27:49.953
And you know it.
You can't go cold turkey,
not alone!

27:50.044 --> 27:52.786
I mean, let me help you,
please!
No!

27:52.880 --> 27:53.869
I love you!

27:55.508 --> 27:57.669
I'll drag you down with me,
I swear to God, I will.

27:57.760 --> 27:58.920
Just leave me alone.

28:00.096 --> 28:01.256
Get out of here!

28:04.600 --> 28:05.589
Now!

28:13.067 --> 28:16.184
REPORTER: An unidentified
Good Samaritan who
witnesses describe

28:16.279 --> 28:17.610
as a young teenage girl

28:17.697 --> 28:20.814
ran into the flames
and rescued the young
lieutenant.

28:21.117 --> 28:24.575
Now the train is registered
to the Nuclear
Regulatory Commission,

28:24.662 --> 28:28.746
and there has been no
official statement yet
as to what was in the car.

28:28.833 --> 28:32.951
Butjudging by the amount
of security around here...

28:40.303 --> 28:42.885
TOM: (ON SPEAKER PHONE)
It wasn’t easy, Nathan,
but consider it gone.

28:42.972 --> 28:45.384
I know I owe you big
on this one, Tom.
I'm not gonna forget it.

28:45.474 --> 28:47.385
Yeah, / won ’t
let you forget it.

28:47.476 --> 28:49.387
Thanks.
Sure thing.

28:49.478 --> 28:51.605
Mom's rap sheet is now
officially buried.

28:51.689 --> 28:55.102
It only took half my political
capital to pull it off.

28:55.192 --> 28:58.650
Why can't she get herself
a hobby like a normal person?

28:58.905 --> 29:00.611
They were married
41 years.

29:01.782 --> 29:03.568
It's a plea
for attention.

29:03.659 --> 29:06.116
She's lonely.
Give her some time, will you?

29:06.203 --> 29:07.363
I don't have time.

29:07.455 --> 29:09.491
I got eight days
to make up ten points.

29:09.582 --> 29:13.166
I need all the help I can get,
which is what I wanna
talk to you about.

29:13.252 --> 29:15.208
I wanna offer
you a job.

29:15.296 --> 29:17.036
A job?
Yeah.

29:17.131 --> 29:19.622
I trust you.
You're good with people.

29:20.259 --> 29:22.841
I need a coordinator to help
organize the volunteers,

29:22.929 --> 29:24.419
and you got
nice guy instincts,

29:24.513 --> 29:25.798
I could use that.

29:25.973 --> 29:29.306
I'm a shark, Pete,
everybody knows it.

29:29.393 --> 29:31.349
And it's starting
to show up in the polls.

29:31.437 --> 29:34.600
I bring you on, and it kind of
reflects well on me,
you know what I mean?

29:34.690 --> 29:37.602
Yeah, all right,
so I make you look good.
That's a new one.

29:37.693 --> 29:40.275
It makes me look like
I put family first.

29:40.363 --> 29:43.605
I mean, I know that sounds
self-serving, but this is
for you, too, right?

29:43.699 --> 29:45.155
You've got to think
of your future.

29:45.242 --> 29:47.278
How do you do that?
Do what?

29:47.370 --> 29:51.113
Even try to make it look
like it has something
to do with me?

29:51.207 --> 29:53.619
You didn't hear
anything that I said
earlier today, did you?

29:53.709 --> 29:55.620
About how you can fly?
Yeah, I did.

29:55.711 --> 29:58.293
I'm gonna pretend for both
our sakes you didn't say
anything like that.

29:58.381 --> 30:00.838
I'm trying to do
the right thing here.

30:00.925 --> 30:02.131
Look, I already have a job.

30:02.218 --> 30:04.960
Yeah, watching old people die,
now there's a career.

30:05.054 --> 30:06.840
It's not cute
anymore, man.

30:06.931 --> 30:11.015
The dreamy kid, sitting in
the back of the classroom,
staring out the window?

30:11.102 --> 30:12.592
It's time for you
to grow up.

30:13.896 --> 30:17.263
Look, I cast
a big shadow,
Pete, I get it.

30:18.234 --> 30:19.565
Life isn't fair.

30:20.277 --> 30:22.734
But there's nothing
I can do about that.

30:22.989 --> 30:26.197
I'm trying to do
the right thing by you
here, okay?

30:26.283 --> 30:28.490
I don't want your pity.

31:02.486 --> 31:06.525
Hey. Corner of
Center and Canal, please.

31:14.832 --> 31:15.912
Wow.

31:18.377 --> 31:19.913
Solar eclipse.

31:20.004 --> 31:23.246
Yeah, yeah, Iwonder
if it's gonna be total.

31:23.340 --> 31:24.716
Not here, no.

31:24.800 --> 31:28.292
Some other part
of the world, yes.
A global event.

31:28.471 --> 31:31.884
Makes one appreciate
just how small our planet
really is.

31:31.974 --> 31:35.182
And we're all quite small
really, aren't we?

31:37.480 --> 31:38.560
What's your name?

31:38.647 --> 31:39.636
Mohinder.

31:40.149 --> 31:41.389
I'm Peter.

31:42.234 --> 31:43.690
Let me ask you something,
Mohinder.

31:43.778 --> 31:46.986
Do you ever get the feeling
like you were meant

31:47.073 --> 31:49.359
to do something
extraordinary?

31:50.993 --> 31:52.949
I'm driving a cab,
you may have noticed.

31:53.037 --> 31:56.655
No, I'm not talking about
what you do, I'm talking
about who you are.

31:56.749 --> 31:59.991
I'm talking about
being special.

32:00.461 --> 32:02.793
Yes, we are all special.

32:03.422 --> 32:05.504
That's not what I meant.

32:13.557 --> 32:15.422
This is natural selection.

32:15.518 --> 32:18.601
It begins as a single
individual born or hatched

32:18.687 --> 32:21.349
like every other member
of their species, anonymous,

32:21.440 --> 32:22.850
seemingly ordinary,

32:24.026 --> 32:25.266
except they're not.

32:25.569 --> 32:28.936
They carry inside them
the genetic code that will
take their species

32:29.031 --> 32:31.522
to the next
evolutionary rung.

32:33.327 --> 32:34.533
It's destiny.

32:40.042 --> 32:42.533
Hey! Hey,

32:42.628 --> 32:45.290
I can't believe
you just left like that!

32:45.548 --> 32:47.880
Yeah, I know,
I was there.

32:47.967 --> 32:50.629
You saved that dude's life,
he was okay!

34:33.489 --> 34:35.150
Welcome home.

34:45.209 --> 34:46.745
Get over there.

34:46.835 --> 34:48.086
Fifty grand is a lot of money.

34:48.170 --> 34:49.159
Fifty?

34:49.588 --> 34:51.579
It was 30.
Even with interest...

34:51.674 --> 34:53.414
Mr. Linderman wants
to be nice about this.

34:53.509 --> 34:56.251
You should have
read the fine print.

34:57.304 --> 35:00.967
Look, I have a son.
I'm all he's got.

35:01.141 --> 35:02.130
Mmm.

35:05.062 --> 35:06.848
Please, I can get you
the money.

35:06.939 --> 35:08.520
I'll tell you
what I'm gonna do.

35:08.607 --> 35:11.223
I'm gonna make you
a little business
proposition.

35:11.318 --> 35:15.527
You make, what, 40 bucks
for every 20 minutes
you take off your clothes?

35:16.198 --> 35:19.611
Well, I'm gonna give you
a chance to lower
your debt a little.

35:19.702 --> 35:22.068
And see where it goes
from there.

35:24.915 --> 35:25.904
Come on.

35:32.715 --> 35:35.001
Come on,
show me what you got.

35:45.269 --> 35:47.225
Lift up your shirt, baby.

35:49.898 --> 35:51.934
Oh, look at that belly.

35:53.444 --> 35:55.059
Smile for me.

35:56.905 --> 35:58.111
That what you want?

35:58.198 --> 35:59.654
Ah, yes.

36:03.120 --> 36:06.829
What's the matter, baby?
You just started
getting good here.

36:06.915 --> 36:08.655
What's the problem, baby?

36:10.419 --> 36:12.910
I said, what's the matter?

36:15.966 --> 36:16.955
Screw you.

36:17.051 --> 36:18.040
Screw me?

