38:42.070 --> 38:45.233
When are you coming to get me?
/ hate it here.

38:45.324 --> 38:48.282
You said you’d be back soon.
Just come pick me up, okay?

39:17.231 --> 39:18.687
(SHUSHING)

39:29.451 --> 39:31.191
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

39:31.286 --> 39:32.446
Hello?
SIMONE: Peter, it’s me.

39:32.538 --> 39:34.699
Hey! Simone?
Are you busy?

39:34.790 --> 39:37.327
No, I was just
heading home.

39:37.501 --> 39:39.082
Listen, I need you
to meet me at my dad’s.

39:39.169 --> 39:41.546
Yeah, no, I can be there
in 10 minutes.

39:41.672 --> 39:43.913
Just hurry, okay?
Yeah, okay, okay,
I'll see you there. Bye.

39:44.007 --> 39:46.339
You know,
I'll hop out here, please.

39:50.222 --> 39:51.211
Thanks.

40:06.822 --> 40:08.358
Where to, my friend?

40:08.448 --> 40:09.574
JFK, please.

40:17.708 --> 40:19.448
I'm going home
to my family.

40:19.543 --> 40:22.080
These business trips
are wearing me out.

40:23.714 --> 40:24.703
Suresh, huh?

40:26.008 --> 40:27.248
I'm sorry?

40:27.676 --> 40:30.463
Your name.
On your license, there.

40:31.763 --> 40:33.469
That's Indian, yes?

40:35.183 --> 40:40.052
There was a Professor Suresh
at the University of Madras,
a geneticist.

40:40.147 --> 40:41.637
Interesting theories.

40:42.024 --> 40:44.686
Don't think he's teaching
anymore.

40:45.527 --> 40:47.643
But you wouldn't know anything
about that, would you?

40:48.822 --> 40:51.188
Probably lots of Sureshes
where you're from.

40:52.075 --> 40:54.908
Like Smith or Anderson.

41:13.722 --> 41:18.216
And then Carla had
the nerve to tell me
he's not breed-worthy.

41:18.852 --> 41:21.969
Like he didn't win
five all-breed rallies,
two regionals.

41:22.064 --> 41:23.645
Can you believe it?

41:23.982 --> 41:26.268
It's just not true,
Mr. Muggles.

41:26.360 --> 41:29.693
It's not true.
He's a little stud muffin,
that's what he is.

41:30.030 --> 41:32.316
He still humps my leg
when I watch TV.

41:32.407 --> 41:35.114
All right, enough
about Mr. Muggles.

41:35.410 --> 41:37.321
What'd everybody else
do today?

41:37.412 --> 41:39.403
Doug and I saw
this Mexican guy.

41:39.498 --> 41:41.238
A homeless dude,
on our way to school.

41:41.792 --> 41:44.329
We thought he was dead,
but he wasn't.

41:45.754 --> 41:47.460
I thought Dad
was coming home today.

41:47.547 --> 41:49.708
Well, ah, Iwas gonna
surprise you.

41:53.095 --> 41:54.960
Just in time to read
my report card.

41:55.055 --> 41:58.138
So what about you, Claire,
do anything special today?

42:03.313 --> 42:05.929
I walked through fire
and I didn't get burned.

42:10.946 --> 42:12.652
What the hell is that
supposed to mean?

42:12.739 --> 42:15.196
God, you're so
crazy sometimes.
Lyle.

42:17.035 --> 42:19.868
I think I know exactly
what you mean.

42:19.955 --> 42:23.072
Oh, here I am,
talking dogs again.

42:23.166 --> 42:26.124
And you go and say
something really profound.

42:27.254 --> 42:30.212
We come up against
all kinds of fires
in our lives,

42:30.298 --> 42:33.461
and when we test ourselves
and face our fears,

42:34.094 --> 42:36.050
we usually
don't get burned.

42:36.304 --> 42:39.011
You are very wise,
sweetheart.

42:39.099 --> 42:43.263
Whatever it is you did,
I'm proud of you.
And so is Mr. Muggles!

42:43.729 --> 42:46.892
He's just so proud of Claire!
Aren't we?
We're proud of Claire.

42:46.982 --> 42:49.348
Yes, we're so proud
of Claire, aren't we?

42:49.484 --> 42:51.020
She's the best.

44:01.515 --> 44:02.721
Hiro.

44:13.902 --> 44:16.314
What are you looking for?

44:16.404 --> 44:17.655
Morphine.

44:17.739 --> 44:19.149
What for?

44:19.491 --> 44:20.981
I need you to come
with me someplace.

44:21.076 --> 44:22.612
Where?
You'll see.

44:23.620 --> 44:25.827
Look, there's...
There's something
I need to tell you.

44:25.914 --> 44:27.779
Now that is gonna
have to wait.

44:27.874 --> 44:30.160
No, look, I need to
tell you about this, okay?

44:30.252 --> 44:32.038
I've gotta stop living
for other people.

44:32.128 --> 44:34.835
My whole life
I've had no idea
what I'm supposed to do,

44:34.923 --> 44:37.585
what I'm supposed
to be, if I even have
a destiny of my own!

44:37.676 --> 44:39.917
I promise you we will
talk about this later, okay?

44:40.011 --> 44:42.502
But right now I really
need you to come with me.

44:42.597 --> 44:46.556
You're a nurse,
you can give out a shot,
you can help him.

44:46.643 --> 44:47.632
Help who?

44:50.105 --> 44:52.721
I thought we could go
to the movies this Saturday,

44:52.983 --> 44:57.773
maybe try on some shoes
at the new mail
in Gardendale.

44:59.906 --> 45:00.895
Sure.

45:03.368 --> 45:04.983
I love you, Mom.

45:06.329 --> 45:07.318
But?

45:11.126 --> 45:12.332
No buts.

45:13.044 --> 45:14.830
I just wanted
to tell you that.

45:15.672 --> 45:18.630
I know you think I'm trying
to be your best friend again,
admit it.

45:18.717 --> 45:19.706
No.

45:20.427 --> 45:24.215
It's all right, we can go
to the movies together.
It's no big deal.

45:24.306 --> 45:27.764
Ijust miss you,
that's all.

45:29.603 --> 45:33.767
I wanna be your mom,
I wanna give you advice.

45:33.940 --> 45:36.477
But I don't wanna
push you away.

45:36.568 --> 45:38.399
I want advice, I do.

45:39.696 --> 45:42.312
I won't push you away,
I promise.

45:47.162 --> 45:51.997
Ijust don't think
you should be so worried
about fitting in all the time.

45:52.834 --> 45:54.950
About being so popular.

45:55.045 --> 45:57.752
I don't want to see you make
mistakes like I did.

45:57.839 --> 46:01.331
I wanted to be someone
more interesting than I am.

46:02.052 --> 46:05.590
You are interesting.
You breed show dogs.
Whose mom does that?

46:06.473 --> 46:09.431
No, I wanted to hitchhike
across Europe.

46:09.809 --> 46:14.519
Study art.
Fall in love with some
poetry-quoting Frenchman.

46:15.106 --> 46:17.848
Not that your dad isn't
wonderful, but my point is,

46:18.276 --> 46:21.609
you should
know who you are
and know that it's enough.

46:21.696 --> 46:24.483
'Cause who you are
is special.

46:27.285 --> 46:28.274
About that.

46:30.538 --> 46:32.665
There's something
I need to say.

46:33.708 --> 46:37.667
Something I never talked about
'cause I thought it would
upset you and Dad.

46:37.879 --> 46:41.371
Sweetheart, you can say
anything to us, you know that.

46:44.135 --> 46:47.047
I think I'm old enough
for you to tell me who
my real parents are.

46:51.184 --> 46:52.469
Of course you are.

46:56.856 --> 46:59.393
Honey! I'm home!

46:59.818 --> 47:01.024
Your father.

47:04.114 --> 47:06.105
Hey,honey!

47:08.034 --> 47:10.821
Bad, Mr. Muggles!
No!

47:13.540 --> 47:15.531
I'm glad you're home.
Oh, me, too.

47:15.625 --> 47:19.083
I have such a headache.
I slammed my head getting
out of a taxicab.

47:19.170 --> 47:20.159
Hi, Daddy!

47:23.091 --> 47:24.581
Hey,baby!

48:39.250 --> 48:40.911
(EXCLAIMING)

48:41.669 --> 48:44.627
Hello, New York!

48:45.465 --> 48:48.252
PETER: I'm just saying
it's impossible. Nobody can
predict the future.

48:48.343 --> 48:51.756
I saw it with my own eyes,
Peter. Isaac! I brought
someone here to help.

48:51.846 --> 48:53.177
He's a nurse.

48:55.100 --> 48:56.089
Isaac.

48:58.686 --> 48:59.675
Isaac?

49:04.025 --> 49:05.014
Isaac?

49:07.362 --> 49:08.351
Isaac!

49:09.489 --> 49:11.195
Simone!

49:11.282 --> 49:13.147
Oh, God!

49:13.243 --> 49:14.232
Okay.

49:14.953 --> 49:16.534
Oh, my God.
Isaac?

49:16.621 --> 49:19.203
